 Large-scale immunization is an essential approach of controlling the pandemic.

Vaccines are now becoming available for protection against pandemic influenza A(H1N1) 2009 infection in some countries.

In response to the pandemic, novel vaccines against the virus strain A/California/07/2009(H1N1) have been developed and recently were approved for vaccination among specific populations in China.

 However, the safety and effectiveness of the vaccines is of prime concern to the authorities and the public.

